reviews.snippet: We randomly ended up here while in search for a full English breakfast. It is a quiet little place with great ambience for a relaxed meal. The service was quick and excellent. The portion sizes were modest but reasonably priced compared to similar places. We only had the English breakfast and a fried chicken bagel which were both delicious.Overall we were pleased and would definitely consider going there again

reviews.snippet:
The atmosphere is amazing — a perfect place to sit and relax with a cup of coffee. The service was quick, efficient, and fantastic.

The food was great in both quality and quantity, definitely worth the price. We had pasta and fries; however, the fries were a bit too oily — something that could be looked into. The frappe was delicious!

The lighting in the café really enhances the ambiance and our pictures turned out beautiful. Overall, a wonderful experience! ,❤️❤️🤩🤩

reviews.snippet:
Randomly found this cafe when we were searching for best cafes in Hyderabad for lunch and trust me this was our best find. Located in a nice quiet location of Jubliee hills this offers both indoors n outdoor sitting options. But as I can't stand cigarette smoke smell we opted for indoor seating.

We being vegetarian, ordered these following items from their list
1. Hot chocolate with marshmallow - just too yummmy
2. Korean Bun - perfectly baked n must try
3. Farmhouse sourdough pizza - super light n made to perfection
4. Peri peri fries - that fiery kick hits the right spots
5. Almond croissant- that warm flaky mildy sweet croissant is worth the hype
6. Basil pesto pasta - it was tasty blend of pesto, olive oil and parmesan cheese with a side serve of soft bread.
7. Berry cheesecake just melts in your mouth with the tangy berry hint in every bite

Would love to go back and try some more of their food, beverages n not to forget their desserts.

reviews.snippet: being a Sunday I preferred to book a table, to avoid disappointment. Checked on Google and there was an option to book a table on their Google my business page. We did book a table for five. Immediately ely got confirmation mail too. On reaching there they said they don’t reserve tables and they never received any intimation from Google. They had to join two table and provide us a sitting arrangement. A bit irritating. Other wise a cool place to hangout with friends casual meeting . The potions are very small and we ended up ordering more number of items. Taste of food is good. There is valet parking which is a blessing in those norrow places.

reviews.snippet:
Disappointed with the Experience

I visited this cafe hoping to enjoy a meal and spend some quiet time working on my laptop, like many people do at cafes. Unfortunately, we were refused service simply because we had our laptops with us. We hadn’t even settled in or asked for charging points—just intended to order food and quietly work for a while.

There was no prior signage or communication about a no-laptop policy, and the way we were asked to leave felt unwelcoming and unfair. A more polite or professional explanation would have been appreciated if there was a genuine policy in place.

As customers, we expect basic courtesy, especially when we’re ready to order and be respectful of the space. Sadly, I won’t be returning, and I hope the management reconsiders how they treat potential patrons in the future.

reviews.snippet:
Had an amazing experience at Theory Patisserie and Café! A special shoutout to Nuel, who went above and beyond to make our visit memorable. Not only was the food absolutely delicious, but Nuel’s service truly stood out - warm, attentive, and genuinely thoughtful. It’s rare to come across someone who takes such pride in their work. He made great recommendations and ensured we were well taken care of throughout.

Nuel definitely deserves recognition and I hope to see him climb up the ranks — his dedication and hospitality are top-notch!

reviews.snippet:
Theory is a cafe I've wanted to visit for a long time! This place is beautiful, especially in the rainy season. The vibe is cozy, warm & it's perfect for any occasion.

They have a diverse menu and Theory is well known for their delicious dessert options.

We tried Butter Chicken Cigars, Cheesy Onion Rings & Cheesy Garlic Bread for starters. We ordered a vegetarian pizza & Alfredo pasta for the main course. All of the dishes were mouthwatering and served quickly.

I'd recommend Theory to anyone looking for a good place to spend time with their friends during this rainy season.

reviews.snippet:
Having been a regular at Theory for quite some time now, I must say it's always held a special place in my heart. Recently, they've revamped their menu, and let me tell you, it's better than ever. The ambiance has this calm, welcoming vibe that just draws you in from the moment you step through the door.

Now, let's talk drinks. Theory doesn't disappoint in this department either. Whether you're into teas, milkshakes or mocktails, they've got something to quench your thirst. And the best part? You get good quality and quantity for the amount you pay.

Sure, they only have one washroom, but hey, at least it's clean! Plus, with the fairy lights twinkling around, it's the perfect setting for a romantic date night.

Now, let's get to the good stuff - desserts! Oh boy, where do I even begin? Their blueberry cheesecake is an absolute must-try, and don't even get me started on the chocolate cake. And if you're into bite-sized treats, their small cupcakes are pretty darn good too.

Oh, and did I mention they offer valet parking? Talk about convenience! Overall, Theory ticks all the boxes for a perfect dining experience, whether you're catching up with friends or treating your special someone to a night out.

reviews.snippet:
I love the ambience of this place. Its decoration and background music are relaxing hence making this venue a perfect place for conversation with friends, dating dinner or enjoying a good coffee as you work alone on your laptop.

The food and beverage menu is large and they have plenty of healthy options along with vegan and gluten-free food. All are available from morning till evening.

Juice and milkshake options are not that extensive but you will find the top classics.

The service is friendly and helpful and free wifi is available.

reviews.snippet:
VERY HUMILIATING SERVICE - Just because I ordered only 2 coffee and a peri peri French fries and a Theory Spl pizza and opened my laptop because of my last minute urgent work call the staff came said sir you "We do not allow work calls in our cafe"  I came at 10:30 and left at 2:30 so as per the management they didn't like the amount of money I spend compared to to the time I spend.

I did ask the staff if they want me to pay extra for the WIFI i was willing to!!!!

The steward said you need to leave as you have been for a very long time and occupying a table!!!!!

This was so humiliating for me, because I came to India after 3 years and wanted to come to a cafe which has a ambiance this is the service I get.

I think you can only come eat and smoke nothing more is allowed, the owner and the management should have a rule board outside the cafe.

Felt so BAD.

reviews.snippet:
Nice ambience, great food (smaller portions though), and very friendly staff.

Not to owner: My main complaint is that they serve 500ml water bottles that are 30 rupees each. These are offered by default as though they are free. I would expect them to offer normal drinking water by default and give me bottled water only when I ask for it. The culture of bottled water, which is a trend post COVID and which most restaurants are now exploiting in the name of hygiene, should go away. Please do your bit to reduce plastic waste.
